  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed replacement fenestration at first floor level, by reason of the chunky and excessive thickness of the proposed frames, as well as the inclusion of uPVC on the rear elevation, will be detrimental and out of character to the appearance of the host building and the wider Barnsbury Conservation Area. The application is therefore contrary to policies D1 (Overall Design), D3 (Site Planning), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), D22 (New Developments in Conservation Areas), D24 (Materials in Conservation Areas) of Islington Council's Unitary Development Plan (2002),  Islington Urban Design Guide (2006), Islington Conservation Area Guidelines (2002), PPS 5: Planning and the Historic Environment and the emerging Islington Core Strategy."
